{
  "stem": "18770.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 17.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I formed my own political views, and I think they have-- I've remained all my life basically-- what is it called today?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A liberal.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, I'm not active in any group, and yet I have strong feelings, you know, about the political state of things.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And certainly I've never lost that awareness.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So artist-- everybody I knew was basically somewhere to the left.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When I hear about kids who were Republicans, I can't-- it boggles the mind, you know, to this day.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "How can a young person be a Republican?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Never have understood and never will.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So we were like that-- liberal, you know, liberal orientation, artist, American.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I mean, I married an American girl.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My children certainly are brought up, you know, I mean here in New-- here.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I keep saying here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I live in LA, but in New York.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But there is always the European connection underneath.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It's always sort of-- that never goes away, you know?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I think it's almost as I get older, I've come back to it, more closer to it again.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think I told you before about the business with my mother, and it's jumping ahead in time, But it's an interesting phenomenon that many years later, as my mother needs somebody to look after her, and a group of-- and is looked after by Polish women in New York who are available and, you know, and who can be hired to work for relatively affordable amounts of money that I find myself having to speak to them in Polish, a language I haven't spoken for 30 years at that point, for all effective purposes.",
      "word_count": 95
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I find that I remember it, that I really understand Polish, that I speak Pol-- that I enjoy it.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
